<br>
However, the purpose of this proposal, is to allow lower level <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to accomplish what I do at 56th with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which is use them to transfer mana between pools, to act as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;mana bus.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
In order to accomplish that, two things are necessary.  First, there has to be a net gain of mana, which is true for the proposed spells, and second the hitpoints lost must be recoverable with a low cost in mana, which I have not demonstrated.<br>
<br>
Yes, currently the only function of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mod Rod</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is to store mana for later.  But I see the flexibility that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> T-Rods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> give me, my group, and raids, and ask: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Is it possible for this role to be extended to lower levels.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Adding charges to the mod rod would actually make things easier, rather than just more convenient.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I am not sure I understand the distinction here.  The proposed two charge mod rod certainly is much better than the current one, but it appears to accomplish my goals, and may not be unreasonable.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For magicians themselves, a T Rod gives 260 mana for 900 hitpoints, ratio of .28. Picking a number of half the efficiency of T Rods, I get that mod rods should give 28 mana for 200 hitpoints, which would mean a mana cost of 122 mana.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Certainly another alternative, and may be better.<br>
<br>
However, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Modulation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does 225 damage, times 14% yields say 32 net mana for a cost of 168 mana per summon.  Either way, I think you can gain 30 mana in no more than three ticks of meditation, making them worthless for mana regeneration.  Further, it leaves no room for a lower level spell to make this role available closer to 30th.  At that level, a net gain of 35 may be more worthwhile, although maybe not<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> BTW please punch in that rod data. I am rather curious.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Ah, okies on a second reading I found it, just a second....PLEASE WAIT....<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
